## Migrations

Use numbered migration files with paired up/down scripts:

```
migrations/
├── 001_initial_schema.up.sql
├── 001_initial_schema.down.sql
├── 002_add_products.up.sql
└── 002_add_products.down.sql
```

Migration standards:
- Wrap each migration in a transaction (`BEGIN; ... COMMIT;`)
- Use `IF NOT EXISTS` / `IF EXISTS` for idempotency
- Add columns with `DEFAULT` before dropping the default if needed (avoid table locks)
- Never drop columns or tables in the same migration that removes references — do it in a follow-up

```sql
-- 002_add_products.up.sql
BEGIN;

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS products (
    id         UUID        PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    name       VARCHAR(200) NOT NULL,
    price      NUMERIC(10,2) NOT NULL CHECK (price >= 0),
    is_active  BOOLEAN      NOT NULL DEFAULT TRUE,
    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
);

CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_products_is_active ON products (is_active);

COMMIT;
```

